headline: Has Intel’s 79.8% 2025 Surge Outrun Its Fundamentals?
summary: If you are wondering whether Intel is still a bargain after its huge run, or if the easy money has already been made, you are in the right place to unpack what the current share price really implies. headline: How a Silicon Valley dealmaker charmed Trump and gave Intel a lifeline
summary: It was a Thursday before dawn in Silicon Valley when Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan found himself under attack by the president of the United States.  “The CEO of INTEL is highly CONFLICTED and must resign, immediately,” U.S. President Donald Trump wrote on his Truth Social platform at 4:39 AM Pacific Time on August 7.  Before he was Intel CEO, Tan had been a prolific investor in companies in China.

headline: Apple CEO Tim Cook Buys $3 Million of Nike Shares. The Stock Is Rising.
summary: Apple  CEO Tim Cook bought nearly $3 million worth of depressed  Nike  stock following the company’s disappointing earnings report last week.  Cook, who is the lead independent director of Nike and a board member since 2005, bought 50,000 shares of Nike stock on Monday at an average price of $58.97, according to a form 4 filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission late Tuesday.  Cook now holds just over 105,000 shares of the footwear maker, worth more than $6 million at Wednesday’s stock price.

headline: Leak Hints at First Intel Nvidia Chip After $5 Billion Partnership
summary: Intel (INTC, Financials) and Nvidia (NVDA, Financials) may be preparing to ship their first jointly developed chip, according to leaked details about a laptop processor called Serpent Lake.  The leak, shared by YouTube channel RedGamingTec, suggests the chip will combine Intel CPUs with Nvidia RTX graphics in a single design.  Serpent Lake is expected to pair Intel's upcoming Titan Lake CPU architecture with Nvidia's RTX Rubin graphics, manufactured on TSMC's 3-nanometer process.
